Generative landscapes on distant mythical planets. The view of the stars, planets, and auroras can be obstructed by a thick atmosphere or overcast weather.

Controls:
1) The keys from '1' to '9' can be used to re-render the artwork, where the number corresponds to the resolution multiplier (e.g., press '4' to render at 4x the initial resolution);
2) 'S' to save.

Features:
1) Time of Day: Night | Day;
2) Mountain: Yes | No;
3) Number of Trees: Ranges from 75 to 125;
4) Height of Trees: Small | Medium | Tall;
5) Hue: Black & White | Any of other 12 hue values;
6) Cloud Cover: Few | Scattered | Broken | Overcast;
7) Planets: Three small planets | Two medium planets | One big planet;
8) Aurora: Yes | No;
9) Atmospheric Density: Thin | Average | Thick.

Made with Vanilla JS
